abstract: >-
  ATLAS (Active-inference Training with Learned Adaptive Stigmergy) is a
  next-generation LLM training architecture built entirely in pure Rust
  with zero external crate dependencies. It fuses four innovations: (1)
  ASTRA-dev, an autonomous research engine that generates live, causal,
  Bayesian-scored training data from NASA/WHO/World Bank APIs at ~10s per
  discovery cycle; (2) GraphPalace, a stigmergic memory palace where
  pheromone trails guide curriculum across training runs (O(1/√T)
  convergence proven in BUTTERS, R²=0.982); (3) TRM-CausalValidator, a
  7M-parameter recursive module that validates causal graphs before corpus
  entry at 0.1% the compute cost of the base model; and (4) ZK Schnorr
  proof chains linking every LLM output to live API data. The result is a
  self-improving scientific intelligence that trains on what it discovers,
  validated by recursive architecture, guided by stigmergic memory.
